$IDEX Faruqi & Faruqi to Lead Ideanomics Investor Suit - Law360 (October 8, 2019) -- Faruqi & Faruqi LLP nabbed the role of lead counsel in New York federal court Monday for a proposed securities class action accusing financial technology company Ideanomics of concealing infrastructure costs that ultimately damaged its financial performance. Pomerantz LLP, The Rosen Law Firm PA and Bragar Eagel & Squire PC had initially thrown their hats in the ring, but backed out in late September, leaving Faruqi's motion unopposed, court records show. The three other firms withdrew their bids after it became clear that investor Jaysukh Rudani, represented by Faruqi, has the largest known financial interest in the outcome of the suit. Bullish

$IDEX Quick thoughts on why recent news isn't moving stock: While positive, most of the news is structural or strategic, not results. The exception, the taxi sales results, while great, only account for ~$1.5MM in revs. For a company with ~$200MM market cap currently, that's not going to move the needle. And there's no clarity on costs, even though we've been told that margins will be high.  With acceleration of sales as well as bigger numbers and more clarity coming in the next few quarterly reports, the future looks amazing. But in the meantime, patience is required. Bullish

Yes, there's some $BTC.X and $ETH.X but trading crypto is not the company plan. The hope for the report is that they can tell us something about what is going on in Q3 and Q4. And while the trade wars don't affect the company directly, the slowing of the China economy as well as the weakening currency exchange rate will affect the revenue projections from buses.  Nevertheless, If there is guidance that is positive enough, it could move the stock substantially. I am here until at least April, and then we shall see. Bullish
